ufacturing agreement uc davis will perform clinical manufacturing and quality control testing of nla on behalf of nohla in the cgmp cell therapy manufacturing facility at the uc davis institute of regenerative cures irc in sacramento california nohla will contribute additional infrastructure to support increased manufacturing capacity at the irc this collaboration will allow the company to manufacture sufficient quantities of nla to supply its clinical trials for hematopoietic cell transplant hct and chemotherapy induced neutropenia cin further collaborative efforts will refine and optimize the nla manufacturing processes a key step in achieving commercial viability nohla therapeutics inc presents at cowen and company th annual health care conference mar  pm feb   nohla therapeutics inc presents at cowen and company th annual health care conference mar  pm venue the boston marriott copley place  huntington avenue boston massachusetts united states speakers colleen delaney founder chief medical officer member of scientific advisory board and member of clinical advisory board nohla therapeutics appoints kathleen fanning as president and chief executive officer and an executive member of the board of directors feb   nohla therapeutics inc announced the appointment of kathleen fanning as president and chief executive officer and an executive member of the board of directors michael sistenich who has been serving as interim chief executive officer will continue in his capacity as a nonexecutive member of the company’s board of directors ms fanning brings to nohla over  years of industry experience holding previous leadership roles in both public and private biopharmaceutical companies she joins nohla after recently serving as chief operating officer at ventirx pharmaceuticals similar private companies by industry company name region n labs inc united states andme inc united states c tech corporation inc united states v biosciences inc united states bar biologics inc unit