e american society of bone marrow transplant and the cord blood association in  she established and became the director of the cord blood transplant program at the fred hutchinson cancer research centerseattle cancer care alliance which has grown to be one of the busiest such programs in the country and the coordinating center of several multicenter clinical trials she is the sponsorinvestigator of three investigational new drug fda files and has been the principal investigator of nine ongoing and completed clinical trials and several ancillary studies dr delaney is also the principal investigator of a research laboratory focused on the role of the notch signaling pathway in hematopoietic stem cell regulation and exvivo expansion of umbilical cord blood stem and progenitor cells for clinical applications her group at fred hutchinson cancer research center developed novel and clinically feasible methods for the ex vivo expansion of cord blood derived hematopoietic stem and progenitor cells in the presence of notch ligands this work was translated into a pilot study investigating the use of ex vivo expanded cord blood progenitors to augment conventional cord blood transplantation she has since extended this work to investigate the potential of cryopreserved nonhla matched “off the shelf” ex vivo expanded cord blood progenitor cells to provide rapid but transient myeloid reconstitution in the setting of cord blood transplant and following doseintensive chemotherapy dr colleen delaney received her md from harvard medical school in  and went on to complete a residency in pediatrics at the university of california san francisco followed by a fellowship in pediatric hematologyoncology at fred hutchinson cancer research centeruniversity of washington dr mark kirkland chief scientific officer mark is a hematologist and stem cell researcher with a wide and varied experience in tissue banking cgmp commercial biotechnology and both public and private pathology mark served as chief science officer at cytomatrix working on developing  various scalable solutions to stem cell expansion his previous roles have included chief of service of geelong hospital pathology service chairman of pathcare consulting pathologists regional transfusion officer and director of research for australian red cross blood service and chief scientific officer for cygenics ltd michael sistenich chief business officer michael is the head of corporate development and responsible for capital raising and major corporate transactions for nohla therapeutics he previously worked as head of corporate development at cytomatrix and  led the life sciences investment banking practice at bell potter securities leading over amn placements through the past year prior to that he held the role of head of healthcare investments at dws investments of deutsche bank in europe and has over  years of experience as a healthcare specialist in international investment management and investment banking jason carstens vice president of manufacturing jason carstens is our vice president of manufacturing and is responsible for process development quality systems and manufacturing operations at nohla therapeutics previously he held the position of staff scientist and director process development and manufacturing at the fred hutchinson cancer research center where he supported the development and manufacture of numerous stem cell and tcell therapeutic products prior to that jason was the director of process development at cmc biologics a contract manufacturing organization where he was involved in the development scaleup and commercialization of more than  different biological drug products he is also active in mentoring undergraduate and graduate students and holds an appointment at the university of washington as an affiliate assistant professor in the department of chemical engineering jason earned a phd from the university of california berkeley and a bs from the university of washington both in the field of chemical engineering darren scotti chief financial officer darren is a cpa with over  years experience specialising in business expansion financial modeling and negotiating darren has honed his skills in a wide range of industries and diverse businesses from large multinationals to small to medium owneroperator concerns darren’s expertise is in wholesale distribution and supply chain gained through his role as cfo with michelin australia and the heat group a combined  years an insolvency specialist with coopers and lybrand and in an investment review role with i the uk’s largest venture capitalist claudia gregorioking clinical operations manager claudia gregorioking has a phd in cord blood biology and has spent the last  years working in the biotechnology field including  years in clinical research organisations as senior project manager she has taken up the position of clinical projects manager and will be planning and implementing clinical trials heather brammer director of program management heather has  years of experience encompassing a broad range of biotechnology expertise from discovery research through gmp scaleup of biologics devices and cell therapies to bla approval and commercialization before joining nohla therapeutics heather served as program manager for the cb transplant program at fred hutchinson cancer research center under dr colleen delaney coordinating development and manufacturing projects and clinical trials related to expanded stem cells derived from cord blood she was also part of a crossfunctional team working on public outreach and education of the lifesaving potential and outcomes of cord blood transplants she initially started out at the hutch in  managing the quality assurance oversight of the gmp cell processing facility prior to that she spent six years at zymogenetics first as a quality control scientist and then as quality assurance manager of commercial products establishing the medical device program and eventually participating in the bla approval and launch of  recothrom® and recothrom® spray kit she started out her biotech career with an internship at icos corp while working on her anthropology degree from university of washington she then moved into a research position in a leukocyte biology lab screening macrophage libraries and developing functional assays and characterization methods of purified proteins guy moeneclaey research manager guy moeneclaey is the research manager for nohla therapeutics guy has worked for many years in biotechnology and specifically haematopoiesis most recently as senior manager of clinical research with miltenyi biotech in europe he brings a wealth of experience to the position and will play a critical role in progressing the core expansion technologies managing our research institute partners and interface into product development benjamin bergo  nohla therapeutics inc  email ceo nohlatherapeuticscom cfo login  day free trial nohla therapeutics inc nohlatherapeuticscom  eastlake avenue east seattle wa  phone na fax na type private employees    revenue    million industry biotechhealthcare sic code   biological products except diagnostic view employees it intelligence news currently hiring historical trends it intelligence no categories no products found helpful hint the inside view displays a list of technologies and products used internally at a company f i r e w a l l show all analytics audiovideo ecommerce os google analytics google analytics shows you the full customer picture across ads and videos websites and social tools tablets and smartphones that makes it easier to serve your current customers and win new ones youtube youtube is a videosharing website created by three former paypal employees in february  and owned by google since late  on which users can upload view and share videos aspdotnetstorefront no description available sign up to see all helpful hint the outside view displays all the technologies and devices which can be 